<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Aalyn Icewindale</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-10-05 12:21:12</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Fellow Clerics..<BR>
<BR>
The powder of Reanimation is NOT a random drop in Unrest.  If it is, then it is extremely rare.  For I know of no one who has obtained it randomly.<BR>
<BR>
The only way to obtain this powder is through Khrix.  He is a mid 30s level Necro hiding in a closet on the 2nd floor.  Originally, you would give him a Fire Beetle Eye to have the Abomination of Khrix spawn.  Now, you must give him a Greater lightstone.<BR>
<BR>
Once you do, Khris will summon the abomination in a cloud of blue magic.  The creature apprears in the room directly behind Khrix. (The room between him and the Recluse room).<BR>
<BR>
The Abomination is a 40th lvl Ghoul who hits in the high double digits, but can easily be taken by 3+ high 30s-low 40s lvl players.<BR>
<BR>
I hope this helps in your quest and may Tunare light your path.<BR>
<BR>
Aalyn Icewindale<BR>
Cleric of the 38th Circle<BR>
Cleric of Tunare<BR>
Cleric of Arcanis Spectare</font></td></tr></table>
